American Superconductor Forecasts Loss as Shipments Refused; Shares Plunge

-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 
2011-04-05T20:13:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/american-superconductor-forecasts-loss-as-shipments-refused-shares-plunge.html
American Superconductor Corp. (AMSC) 
expects to report a loss in its fiscal fourth quarter after
Sinovel Wind Group Co. refused to accept shipments of wind
turbine components.  American Superconductor anticipates total revenue for the
quarter of less than $42 million, it said in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Will Wade in New York at 
